ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me now check a few more things to complete my review:\n1. The BDD
infrastructure step definitions to see if they\'re actually implemented or just 
stubs\n2. Check if `docs/QUALITY_SCORE.md` exists (required by docscheck)\n3. Ch
eck if `prd/v1-infrastructure-bootstrap.md` exists (referenced in exec plan)\n4.
Check a few more API modules for completeness\n5. Check the blocks entity and dt
o\n\nAlso, I noticed that `docker-compose.yml` sets `API_BASE_URL: http://api:30
01` for admin, but doesn\'t include `/api/v1`. So the admin dashboard calling `/
admin/users` would hit `http://api:3001/admin/users`, but the API has global pre
fix `api/v1` making the actual endpoint `http://api:3001/api/v1/admin/users`. Th
is is definitely a bug.\n\nWait, let me re-check. The AdminController is `@Contr
oller("admin/users")` and main.ts sets `app.setGlobalPrefix("api/v1")`. So the a
ctual endpoint is `/api/v1/admin/users`. But the admin dashboard calls `api.get(
\'/admin/users\')` with baseURL `http://api:3001` or `http://localhost:3001`. So
it would hit `/admin/users` without the `/api/v1` prefix. This is a mismatch.\n\
nLet me also check the auth endpoint. The OpenAPI spec says `/api/v1/auth/login`
. The AuthController is `@Controller("api/v1/auth")`. With global prefix, it bec
omes `/api/v1/api/v1/auth/login`. But the generated mobile models and shared typ
es would expect `/api/v1/auth/login`. This is also a bug.\n\nWait, I should veri
fy what the generated auth API client uses for base path. Let me check the gener
ated Dart and TS code.',
    encrypted=None
)
